European stocks advanced, led by
banks and utilities companies.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index climbed 0.3 percent to 267.77 at
10:14 a.m. in  London . The index was little changed earlier
today, rising less than 0.1 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
